creator: OneStep Recovery
descriptionHtml:
OneStep assists people through physical recovery by using everyday sensors to provide ongoing gait diagnostics with the goal of reducing healthcare costs and improving the quality of life. Starting with the smartphone, and expanding to an array of sensors around us, OneStep offers continuous progress feedback and a direct connection to a therapist.


OneStep’s initial target market is physical therapy for people recovering from a stroke and is available for select patients and therapists. Our AI-powered mobile software platform continuously detects and analyzes gait through a smartphone’s sensors, turning the smartphone into a gait lab equivalent - making it available anytime, anywhere. OneStep liberates therapy from inside clinic walls to include activity in patients’ natural environments, updating physical therapists on their patients’ progress at home and allowing them to prescribe supervised exercises 24/7. Patients are empowered through real-time feedback and quantification of their progress, which motivates them toward continued healing.


OneStep is currently being used by clinics and patients across Israel, already improving outcomes.
descriptionShort: Helping patients on the road to recovery, step by step.

title: OneStep

creator: OneStep Recovery
descriptionHtml:
Get better, faster.

Simply download OneStep, place the phone in your pocket and start walking. We'll track and analyze your gait, giving you insight into your walking habits, and progress updates as you improve. You'll also have access to our PTs for online consultations, as well as access to personalized exercise plans.



*About OneStep*

OneStep makes physical therapy effective and accessible by utilizing smartphone sensors as ongoing health diagnostics.
Our mobile app transforms the smartphone into a medical-grade gait lab, offering immediate gait detection and comprehensive analysis that therapists and patients can view anywhere, anytime. Using the app, they can then create personalized treatment plans and receive continuous progress feedback. OneStep empowers patients with an understanding of their own walking habits and motivates them to exercise to contribute to a faster and more complete recovery.

OneStep liberates therapy, allowing therapists to help more patients achieve better clinical outcomes. As new sensors emerge in the devices we all use, we are committed to staying one step ahead to continue providing state-of-the-art, ongoing health diagnostics for better care.

title: OneStep

creator: OneStep Recovery
descriptionHtml:
OneStep is pioneering modern physical therapy - designed for the patient, focused on measurable outcomes and convenient for your everyday life.

No traffic. No appointments. Just you and your smartphone. OneStep takes the hassle out of physical therapy so that you can spend more time with the people and things you love.

Why OneStep?

Outcome-based: OneStep is the only platform in the world that allows you to measure your improvement and get actionable real-time feedback using only a smartphone.

Patient-centered: Your recovery plan is tailored to your needs by a physical therapist and personal care team who get to know you and are available for you at your convenience.

Always-on: Your recovery is happening 24/7, and we think your physical therapy should be, too. Our technology analyzes every step you take so we can help you improve around the clock.

*How it works:*

Our first mobile app transforms the smartphone into a medical-grade gait lab, offering immediate gait detection and comprehensive analysis for therapists and patients, 24/7.

To get started, all the patient needs to do to start is download the app and take a walk with the phone. OneStep immediately analyzes and provides feedback on their walk, empowering patients with an understanding of their gait. Based on their specific recovery goals and gait analysis, OneStep’s expert therapists build each patient a personalized therapy plan.

Patients can perform their daily exercises at any time, or simply open the app and take a walk with guidance. Throughout their journey, patients can utilize OneStep to measure their progress in a quantifiable way, and to receive customized feedback from their care team, which motivates them to exercise better and recover faster.

OneStep works with therapists worldwide as a tool for improving the patient-therapist relationship. Now therapists can communicate with patients 24/7, and provide online and offline exercises, feedback and tests at the most effective times.

creator: OneStep Recovery
descriptionHtml:
OneStep is pioneering modern physical therapy - designed for the patient, focused on measurable outcomes and convenient for your everyday life.

No traffic. No appointments. Just you and your smartphone. OneStep takes the hassle out of physical therapy so that you can spend more time with the people and things you love.

Why OneStep?

Outcome-based: OneStep is the only platform in the world that allows you to measure your improvement and get actionable real-time feedback using only a smartphone.

Patient-centered: Your recovery plan is tailored to your needs by a physical therapist and personal care team who get to know you and are available for you at your convenience.

Always-on: Your recovery is happening 24/7, and we think your physical therapy should be, too. Our technology analyzes every step you take so we can help you improve around the clock.

*How it works:*

Our first mobile app transforms the smartphone into a medical-grade gait lab, offering immediate gait detection and comprehensive analysis for therapists and patients, 24/7.

To get started, all the patient needs to do to start is download the app and take a walk with the phone. OneStep immediately analyzes and provides feedback on their walk, empowering patients with an understanding of their gait. Based on their specific recovery goals and gait analysis, OneStep’s expert therapists build each patient a personalized therapy plan.

Patients can perform their daily exercises or walks at any time, and OneStep will provide them with real-time feedback on their movement and personalized insights on how to improve. Throughout their recovery journey, patients can see their progress in a quantifiable manner, and engage in continuous contact with their care team, which helps them to perform better and recover faster.

OneStep works with therapists and physicians worldwide as a tool for improving the patient-therapist relationship. Now therapists can communicate with patients 24/7, and provide online and offline exercises, feedback and tests at the most effective times.

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
Updates to this version:

Say hi to Rachel! 👋🏼 Rachel is the woman behind the voice you hear in the app. We replaced our computer generated voice with a real person from our team! Rachel is REALLY nice, and she can't wait for you to record your daily walk!

✨ Beautification ✨ Seriously, we dolled the app up a bit. Because we love design as much as we love PT.

Don't forget to leave us a review!

See you inside!

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
Introducing your Walk Score!
Our science and PT teams, joined together to bring you our fabulous new walk score. Now when you take a walk, you will receive an overall walk score, that sums up all the parameters of your walk - BUT - in just ONE number! No several parameters to track, just one easy score, which will quickly show you how your walk is improving!

Always-on: Your recovery is happening 24/7, and we think your physical therapy should be, too. Our technology analyzes every step you take so we can help you improve around the clock.

*How it works:*

Our first mobile app transforms the smartphone into a medical-grade gait lab, offering immediate gait detection and comprehensive analysis for therapists and patients, 24/7.

To get started, all the patient needs to do to start is download the app and take a walk with the phone. OneStep immediately analyzes and provides feedback on their walk, empowering patients with an understanding of their gait. Based on their specific recovery goals and gait analysis, OneStep’s expert therapists build each patient a personalized therapy plan.

Patients can perform their daily exercises or walks at any time, and OneStep will provide them with real-time feedback on their movement and personalized insights on how to improve. Throughout their recovery journey, patients can see their progress in a quantifiable manner, and engage in continuous contact with their care team, which helps them to perform better and recover faster.

OneStep works with therapists and physicians worldwide as a tool for improving the patient-therapist relationship. Now therapists can communicate with patients 24/7, and provide online and offline exercises, feedback and tests at the most effective times.

title: OneStep

creator: OneStep Digital Physical Therapy
descriptionHtml:
You Get:
+ unlimited one-on-one physical therapy sessions + chat with licensed PTs
+ Continuous gait analysis and feedback (gait improvement - even years after joint surgery!)
+ Real-time insights into your PT recovery
+ Personalized Recovery Plans written just for you and adapted as you need
+ Around-the-clock support from OneStep Specialists

-------------

We know that you rely on your body and when your body breaks down it’s more than just pain and inconvenience. It’s a significant barrier to having a life you love. We also know that you have the potential to heal, and that with the right guidance and motivation, you’ll get there. That’s where OneStep comes in.

Why choose OneStep?

OneStep is focused on results.
The only PT app that allows you to measure your progress on your own with meaningful, easy-to-understand feedback and real-time insights. We give you the tools to know exactly how you're doing, to get you better faster.

OneStep is here for you, where ever you are.
Unlimited meetings with a licensed PT who'll write you a personalized recovery plan and be available for continuous communication, to answer your questions, adapt your exercises and ultimately, get you back to your life.

OneStep is convenient and hassle-free.
No traffic. No waiting. Just you and your smartphone, anytime, anywhere. We break your recovery down into small daily sessions, because doing a little bit everyday creates a journey to recovery that turns into results.

-------------

Get Started with OneStep Now:

Step 1 → Download the app and sign up, then stick the phone in your pocket, and take a short walk. OneStep immediately analyzes and provides feedback on your walk, empowering you with a comprehensive understanding of your gait and providing you with a daily walk score, always giving you a sense of where you are today, and how far you’ve come.

Step 2 → Schedule to meet with your OneStep physical therapist who, based on your data and goals, will build you a personalized recovery plan, broken down into small, daily exercises, designed to get you where you want to go. 

Step 3 → Begin your PT! Your daily recovery plan is always there for you on your app. Do your daily PT on your own time, and reach out to chat or connect with your physical therapist whenever you need.

The road to your recovery has never been easier.

Step 3 → Begin your PT! Your daily recovery plan is always there for you on your app. Do your daily PT on your own time, and reach out to chat or connect with your physical therapist whenever you need.

The road to your recovery has never been easier.

descriptionShort: Telemedicine for joint replacement, injuries and MSK disease
title: OneStep, digital physical therapy

creator: OneStep Digital Physical Therapy
descriptionHtml:
OneStep - physical therapy as it should be.

OneStep is an app-based physical therapy service that puts a licensed physical therapist by your side and a motion analysis lab in your pocket. We're here to help you move your body with health, with freedom and with confidence.

We know that you rely on your body and when your body breaks down it’s more than just pain and inconvenience. It’s a significant barrier to having a life you love. We also know that you have the potential to heal and that with the right guidance and motivation, you’ll get there. That’s where OneStep comes in.

The only digital physical therapy platform with proven results in all areas of physical recovery:
* Hip and knee replacement - accelerate your recovery, improve your outcomes, prepare for surgery and even avoid it altogether.
* Neurological rehabilitation - Recovering from a stroke, spine injury, or other condition? Improve your balance, coordination, and alignment from the comfort of your home.
* Chronic pain or limited mobility - Reduce pain and improve range of motion within weeks, even years after the injury.

Why OneStep for physical therapy?
* See the results of your efforts, with OneStep's exclusive smartphone motion lab.
* Get professional support, from dedicated licensed physical therapists with big hearts.
* Recover from anywhere, with a personalized recovery plan that easily fits your day-to-day.

Some quick OneStep stats:
* 9 in 10 members consider OneStep to be essential to their recovery.
* 72% complete their full course of care, with industry-high adherence and compliance.
* 93% successfully achieve their therapy goals and report reduced pain, increased mobility and better quality of life.

Start your 14-day free trial now
* Then starting at $35 / month. No hidden costs and cheaper than your copay.
* HSA / FSA cards accepted.
* Start now, cancel anytime, no strings attached.

Get started with 5 easy steps:
1. Download the app and get your walk evaluation in 30 seconds
2. Meet your personal physical therapist
3. Start recovering with a personalized daily exercise plan
4. Get feedback in real-time
5. Watch yourself improve

We value your privacy
OneStep prides itself on its commitment to patient privacy. We use the highest encryption and privacy standards to ensure that your data is and will always be safe and private. OneStep is HIPAA compliant.

Want to learn more? Check out our FAQs
https://www.onestep.co/faq

Learn about OneStep success stories
https://www.onestep.co/service/stories

Follow us on social media
https://www.facebook.com/onestephealth
https://www.instagram.com/onestep_pt/

Privacy and Terms
https://www.onestep.co/terms-and-conditions
https://www.onestep.co/privacy-policy-2

creator: OneStep Digital Physical Therapy
descriptionHtml:
OneStep - physical therapy as it should be.

Join thousands of users who are already benefiting from our physical therapy platform. Licensed physical therapists will guide you through your treatment and recovery; meeting with you regularly, helping you set your goals, and continuously adapting your personalized recovery plan. OneStep provides you with meaningful, easy-to-understand feedback, based on clinical-grade motion analysis directly from your smartphone. OneStep is designed to easily fit into your day-to-day life - your exercise plan is always one click away, no matter where you are.

OneStep is an app-based physical therapy service that puts a licensed physical therapist by your side and a motion analysis lab in your pocket. We're here to help you move your body with health, with freedom and with confidence.

We know that you rely on your body and when your body breaks down it’s more than just pain and inconvenience. It’s a significant barrier to having a life you love. We also know that you have the potential to heal, and that with the right guidance and motivation, you’ll get there. That’s where OneStep comes in.

The only digital physical therapy platform with proven results in all areas of physical recovery:

* Hip and knee replacement - accelerate your recovery, improve your outcomes, prepare for surgery and even avoid it altogether.

* Neurological rehabilitation - Recovering from a stroke, spine injury, or other condition? Improve your balance, coordination, and alignment from the comfort of your home.

* Chronic pain or limited mobility - Reduce pain and improve range of motion within weeks, even years after the injury.


Why OneStep for physical therapy?

* See the results of your efforts, with OneStep's exclusive smartphone motion lab.

* Get professional support, from dedicated licensed physical therapists with big hearts.

* Recovery from anywhere, with a personalized recovery plan that easily fits your day-to-day.


Some quick OneStep stats:

* 9 in 10 members consider OneStep to be essential to their recovery.

* 93% successfully achieve their therapy goal and report reduced pain, increased mobility, and better life.

OneStep physical therapists come from all over the world and are licensed in the US, UK, and more. title: Physical Therapy by OneStep

creator: OneStep Digital Physical Therapy
descriptionHtml:
OneStep is an FDA-listed medical app that uses smartphone motion sensors to provide immediate, clinically-validated feedback on gait and mobility — no wearables or calibration necessary. Providers and clinicians across the US are using OneStep to drive patient engagement, monitor mobility, identify fall risk, and deliver highly-personalized remote care.

OneStep's smartphone-based motion analysis — the OneStep app is able to capture real-world movement during everyday activities such as walking, running, and negotiating stairs. Additionally, using the app patients can record joint range of motion and standardized functional mobility assessments. Results are shared with the patient and automatically transmitted to the OneStep clinician portal for remote therapeutic monitoring (RTM).

OneStep’s innovative virtual care and remote therapeutic monitoring technology is based on sophisticated motion science that provides immediate, clinically-validated feedback on gait and mobility and enables proactive, data-driven care that transcends in-person visits.

— Learn more at www.onestep.co

Key In-app OneStep Features:

- Active and passive gait analyses
- ROM measurements and standardized tests (TUG, STS, and more)
- Patient-reported outcome measures (LEFS, PSFS, and more)
- Easy-to-follow and customizable daily home exercise programs
- Video, audio, and text messaging for ongoing communication
- Synchronous virtual visit capabilities
- Patient progress reports and insights

Why OneStep?

- Enhance clinical insight. OneStep empowers actionable insight based on heightened visibility into patient mobility, health, and risk status that optimizes patient assessment and care management.
- Boost patient engagement: OneStep motivates patients with actionable feedback, ongoing communication with their providers, convenient virtual care options, and easy-to-follow routines — improving clinical outcomes, adherence, and retention.
- Capture objective evidence. OneStep equips providers with evidence to justify medical necessity and establish clinical excellence by capturing patient progress or risk profile and clearly documenting the efficacy of devices and interventions.

Providers and clinicians across the US are using OneStep to drive patient engagement, monitor mobility, identify fall risk, and deliver highly-personalized remote care.

OneStep's smartphone-based motion analysis — the OneStep app is able to capture real-world movement during everyday activities such as walking, running, and negotiating stairs. Additionally, using the app patients can record joint range of motion and standardized functional mobility assessments. Results are shared with the patient and automatically transmitted to the OneStep clinician portal for remote therapeutic monitoring (RTM).

OneStep’s innovative virtual care and remote therapeutic monitoring technology is based on sophisticated motion science that provides immediate, clinically-validated feedback on gait and mobility and enables proactive, data-driven care that transcends in-person visits.

— Learn more at www.onestep.co

Key In-app OneStep Features:

- Active and passive gait analyses
- ROM measurements and standardized tests (TUG, STS, and more)
- Patient-reported outcome measures (LEFS, PSFS, and more)
- Easy-to-follow and customizable daily home exercise programs
- Video, audio, and text messaging for ongoing communication
- Synchronous virtual visit capabilities
- Patient progress reports and insights

Why OneStep?

- Enhance clinical insight. OneStep empowers actionable insight based on heightened visibility into patient mobility, health, and risk status that optimizes patient assessment and care management.
- Boost patient engagement: OneStep motivates patients with actionable feedback, ongoing communication with their providers, convenient virtual care options, and easy-to-follow routines — improving clinical outcomes, adherence, and retention.
- Capture objective evidence. OneStep equips providers with evidence to justify medical necessity and establish clinical excellence by capturing patient progress or risk profile and clearly documenting the efficacy of devices and interventions.

OneStep helps providers:

- Prevent falls and complications
- Strengthen documentation with objective data
- Improve patient engagement and outcomes
- Facilitate hybrid care models

OneStep helps patients:

- Stay motivated with immediate motion feedback
- Feel connected through seamless communication
- Play an active role in their care plan

Movement is a critical indicator of health. Leading organizations across the US are using OneStep to leverage mobility insight like never before - improving the care experience for patients and providers alike.

OneStep is a digital care solution powered by smartphone motion intelligence and equipped with all the tools needed to assess, treat, and monitor patients both in person and remotely. OneStep's comprehensive digital platform empowers providers with heightened visibility into patient mobility so that they can deliver the most precise and proactive care possible.

OneStep helps providers:

- Prevent falls and complications
- Strengthen documentation with objective data
- Improve patient engagement and outcomes
- Facilitate hybrid care models

OneStep helps patients:

- Stay motivated with immediate motion feedback
- Feel connected through seamless communication
- Play an active role in their care plan

Movement is a critical indicator of health. Leading organizations across the US are using OneStep to leverage mobility insight like never before - improving the care experience for patients and providers alike.

Dual Task - New optional recording flow.
New optional activity summary without gait parameters.
Bug fixes and stability improvements.
